I believe things are going to be a bit cold between them at first, but I truly hope they’ll end up being friends, just to shut you all up.

after the brutal deaths of their fathers and elder brothers

her upbringing by the just ned and cat will allow her to rule the north with some ease

summary: Do you think sansa's physical resemblance to catelyn would be an important part of the northern lords recognizing her as the...
question: Do you think sansa's physical resemblance to catelyn would be an important part of the northern lords recognizing her as the real sansa stark? Since, unlike the rest of her siblings and jon, she doesn't have her direwolf to vouch for her (i'm assuming that arya would go north after reuniting with nymeria in the riverlands).
answer:
Oh, definitely.  Sansa’s looks are very recognizable - I mean, she really isn’t getting away with much in the Vale with her brown hair.  Her thoroughly rinsing the dye from her hair is going to be a huge act of taking her identity back.  

(Despite the hair, the Royces definitely already have a few hints… especially if we’re going by the backstory Petyr has given Alayne.)


“I was teasing. Your mother was a gentlewoman of Braavos, daughter of a merchant prince. We met in Gulltown when I had charge of the port. She died giving you birth, and entrusted you to the Faith. I have some devotional books you can look over. Learn to quote from them. Nothing discourages unwanted questions as much as a flow of pious bleating. In any case, at your flowering you decided you did not wish to be a septa and wrote to me. That was the first I knew of your existence.” He fingered his beard. “Do you think you can remember all that?” 

Myranda gave her a shrewd little smile. “Yes, she was the very soul of wisdom, that good lady.” She shifted her seat. “Why must mules be so bony and ill-tempered? Mya does not feed them enough. A nice fat mule would be more comfortable to ride. There’s a new High Septon, did you know? Oh, and the Night’s Watch has a boy commander, some bastard son of Eddard Stark’s.”“Jon Snow?” she blurted out, surprised.“Snow? Yes, it would be Snow, I suppose.”

She… isn’t exactly keeping her cover.  Between Nestor, Randa, and Bronze Yohn, something is bound to happen to reveal her identity soon enough!

Oh, definitely.  Sansa’s looks are very recognizable - I mean, she really isn’t getting away with much in the Vale with her brown hair.  Her thoroughly rinsing the dye from her hair is going to be a huge act of taking her identity back.  

(Despite the hair, the Royces definitely already have a few hints… especially if we’re going by the backstory Petyr has given Alayne.)


“I was teasing. Your mother was a gentlewoman of Braavos, daughter of a merchant prince. We met in Gulltown when I had charge of the port. She died giving you birth, and entrusted you to the Faith. I have some devotional books you can look over. Learn to quote from them. Nothing discourages unwanted questions as much as a flow of pious bleating. In any case, at your flowering you decided you did not wish to be a septa and wrote to me. That was the first I knew of your existence.” He fingered his beard. “Do you think you can remember all that?” 

Myranda gave her a shrewd little smile. “Yes, she was the very soul of wisdom, that good lady.” She shifted her seat. “Why must mules be so bony and ill-tempered? Mya does not feed them enough. A nice fat mule would be more comfortable to ride. There’s a new High Septon, did you know? Oh, and the Night’s Watch has a boy commander, some bastard son of Eddard Stark’s.”“Jon Snow?” she blurted out, surprised.“Snow? Yes, it would be Snow, I suppose.”

She… isn’t exactly keeping her cover.  Between Nestor, Randa, and Bronze Yohn, something is bound to happen to reveal her identity soon enough!

Sansa: come on, you love it

Sansa: it’s great. It works everytime

Arya: it’s humiliating

Sansa: do you have a better plan?

Arya: no

Sansa: we’re doing it

Arya: we are not doing ‘get help’

*several minutes later*

Sansa, dragging Arya: Get help! Please! My sister is dying! Get help! Help her!

Sansa: *throws Arya at a few guards, knocking them over*

Sansa: classic!

Arya, getting up: I still hate it. It’s humiliating

Sansa: not for me, it’s not
